
[1]algaroth

   AL'GAROT, or AL'GAROTH, n. The name of an emetic powder, prepared from
   the regulus of antimony, dissolved in acids, and separated by repeated
   lotions in warm water. It is either an Arabic term, or the name of the
   inventor, a physician of Verona.
